# Code Review Checklist

## Before approving, verify

### Correctness
- [ ] No `dynamic` / `// ignore` without a comment.
- [ ] Names self-explanatory.
- [ ] Functions do one thing, ≤3 args.
- [ ] Errors handled (not swallowed) and surfaced in brand voice.
- [ ] No `print()` / leftover `debugPrint`.

### Architecture
- [ ] Repository pattern respected: no Supabase SDK calls in widgets/notifiers (adr-0008-data-access-repository-pattern-for-portability).
- [ ] Feature-first folder structure (adr-0010-folder-structure-feature-first-vs-layer-first).
- [ ] No new circular dependencies between features.

### Tests
- [ ] Tests pass.
- [ ] New behavior covered by at least one test.
- [ ] No tests of trivial getters.

### Security
- [ ] No secrets committed. `.env` in `.gitignore`.
- [ ] RLS on any new table. Server-side validation in RPCs.
- [ ] No service-role key in client code.

### Performance
- [ ] No new O(n²) loops on user-facing paths.
- [ ] Long lists use `ListView.builder` / `SliverList.builder`.
- [ ] Images via `cached_network_image`.
- [ ] `const` constructors where the analyzer suggests.

### Accessibility
- [ ] `Semantics` on new interactive elements.
- [ ] Tap targets ≥44pt.
- [ ] Contrast verified (4.5:1 body).

### Hygiene
- [ ] Conventional commit message proposed.
- [ ] Dead code deleted.
- [ ] No new TODO without owner + date.


